Similar numbers to last week as Singleton agents penned 825 head. Quality remained high throughout the young cattle, export types very mixed with a lot of single sales. Not all of the regular processing orders in play however firm to dearer sentiments were obtained for most grades.
 
Weaner steers saw a spike of 68c/kg selling from 302c to 466c/kg however over 330kg lacked support from both re-stocker and trade orders making from 285c to 378c/kg. Weaner heifers up by 14c/kg selling from 256c to 340c/kg while medium and heavier types lacked a great deal of interest making from 230c to 316c/kg the latter for B muscle Butcher calves.
 
Yearling steers headed for the paddock saw little change selling from 324c to 355c/kg similar quote for heifer counterparts 250c to 308c/kg. Less than 50 cows on offer 2 scores 200c to 258c/kg, heavy 3 and 4 scores up 12c/kg trading from 254c to 280c/kg.
 
Market Operator Angus Barlow.
